{"title":"Water use vs groundwater recharge — Yucatán Peninsula","markdown":{"yaml":{"draft":false,"title":"Water use vs groundwater recharge — Yucatán Peninsula","description":"Water balance dashboard comparing total water demand against natural groundwater recharge across the Yucatán Peninsula, including projections to 2030 under different climate and development scenarios.","date":"2020-01-01","date-modified":"2020-01-01","categories":["Visualisation","Interactive","Tableau","Water","Hydrology","Mexico"],"image":"../../assets/images/img-scatter.svg","format":{"html":{"page-layout":"full"}}},"headingText":"How to read it","containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n\n[← Back to Portfolio](../../portfolio.html){.back-link}\n\n::: {.label}\nInteractive · Water Balance · Yucatán Peninsula · MuSIASEM · 2015–2030\n:::\n\nThis is the core output visualisation from the doctoral research on water societal metabolism in the Yucatán Peninsula. It puts supply and demand on the same axis: how much water naturally recharges the karst aquifer through rainfall infiltration each year, and how much the economy — agriculture, tourism, industry, households — extracts from it.\n\nThe two lines can be read like a scissors: recharge is falling under most climate projections (around 23% less by 2030 under central estimates), while demand is growing as the economy shifts toward water-intensive activities. The point where demand approaches or exceeds recharge is not a theoretical endpoint but a near-term planning constraint in some sub-regions.\n\n\nThe balance view shows the gap between supply and demand by sub-region and scenario. The scenario explorer lets you toggle between different combinations of economic development pathway and climate trajectory. Negative balances — demand exceeding recharge — are shown in red.\n\n## Methods\n\nRecharge estimated from a monthly water balance model calibrated against 40 years of historical data, then projected using four downscaled General Circulation Models. Demand estimated via MuSIASEM (Multi-Scale Integrated Analysis of Societal and Ecosystem Metabolism) using employment structure, water intensity coefficients, and demographic projections.\n\nFull methodology in: Rodríguez-Huerta, E., Rosas-Casals, M. & Hernández-Terrones, L.M. (2019). *Journal of Cleaner Production*, 235, 272–287. [doi:10.1016/j.jclepro.2019.06.310](https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jclepro.2019.06.310)\n\n::: {.column-screen}\n\n```{=html}\n<div class=\"tableauPlaceholder\" id=\"viz2003\" style=\"position: relative\">\n  <noscript>\n    <a href=\"https://public.tableau.com/app/profile/edgar.rodriguez.huerta/viz/WaterusevsrechargeofgroundwaterinYucatan/BLEWF\">\n      <img alt=\"BLEWF\" src=\"https://public.tableau.com/static/images/Wa/WaterusevsrechargeofgroundwaterinYucatan/BLEWF/1_rss.png\" style=\"border: none\">\n    </a>\n  </noscript>\n  <object class=\"tableauViz\" style=\"display:none;\">\n    <param name=\"host_url\" value=\"https%3A%2F%2Fpublic.tableau.com%2F\">\n    <param name=\"embed_code_version\" value=\"3\">\n    <param name=\"site_root\" value=\"\">\n    <param name=\"name\" value=\"WaterusevsrechargeofgroundwaterinYucatan/BLEWF\">\n    <param name=\"tabs\" value=\"no\">\n    <param name=\"toolbar\" value=\"yes\">\n    <param name=\"static_image\" value=\"https://public.tableau.com/static/images/Wa/WaterusevsrechargeofgroundwaterinYucatan/BLEWF/1.png\">\n    <param name=\"animate_transition\" value=\"yes\">\n    <param name=\"display_static_image\" value=\"yes\">\n    <param name=\"display_spinner\" value=\"yes\">\n    <param name=\"display_overlay\" value=\"yes\">\n    <param name=\"display_count\" value=\"yes\">\n    <param name=\"language\" value=\"en-GB\">\n  </object>\n</div>\n<script type=\"text/javascript\">\n  var divElement = document.getElementById('viz2003');\n  var vizElement = divElement.getElementsByTagName('object')[0];\n  if (divElement.offsetWidth > 800) { vizElement.style.width = '100%'; vizElement.style.height = '827px'; }\n  else if (divElement.offsetWidth > 500) { vizElement.style.width = '100%'; vizElement.style.height = '827px'; }\n  else { vizElement.style.width = '100%'; vizElement.style.height = '727px'; }\n  var scriptElement = document.createElement('script');\n  scriptElement.src = 'https://public.tableau.com/javascripts/api/viz_v1.js';\n  vizElement.parentNode.insertBefore(scriptElement, vizElement);\n</script>\n```\n\n:::\n","srcMarkdownNoYaml":"\n\n[← Back to Portfolio](../../portfolio.html){.back-link}\n\n::: {.label}\nInteractive · Water Balance · Yucatán Peninsula · MuSIASEM · 2015–2030\n:::\n\nThis is the core output visualisation from the doctoral research on water societal metabolism in the Yucatán Peninsula. It puts supply and demand on the same axis: how much water naturally recharges the karst aquifer through rainfall infiltration each year, and how much the economy — agriculture, tourism, industry, households — extracts from it.\n\nThe two lines can be read like a scissors: recharge is falling under most climate projections (around 23% less by 2030 under central estimates), while demand is growing as the economy shifts toward water-intensive activities. The point where demand approaches or exceeds recharge is not a theoretical endpoint but a near-term planning constraint in some sub-regions.\n\n## How to read it\n\nThe balance view shows the gap between supply and demand by sub-region and scenario. The scenario explorer lets you toggle between different combinations of economic development pathway and climate trajectory. Negative balances — demand exceeding recharge — are shown in red.\n\n## Methods\n\nRecharge estimated from a monthly water balance model calibrated against 40 years of historical data, then projected using four downscaled General Circulation Models. Demand estimated via MuSIASEM (Multi-Scale Integrated Analysis of Societal and Ecosystem Metabolism) using employment structure, water intensity coefficients, and demographic projections.\n\nFull methodology in: Rodríguez-Huerta, E., Rosas-Casals, M. & Hernández-Terrones, L.M. (2019). *Journal of Cleaner Production*, 235, 272–287. [doi:10.1016/j.jclepro.2019.06.310](https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jclepro.2019.06.310)\n\n::: {.column-screen}\n\n```{=html}\n<div class=\"tableauPlaceholder\" id=\"viz2003\" style=\"position: relative\">\n  <noscript>\n    <a href=\"https://public.tableau.com/app/profile/edgar.rodriguez.huerta/viz/WaterusevsrechargeofgroundwaterinYucatan/BLEWF\">\n      <img alt=\"BLEWF\" src=\"https://public.tableau.com/static/images/Wa/WaterusevsrechargeofgroundwaterinYucatan/BLEWF/1_rss.png\" style=\"border: none\">\n    </a>\n  </noscript>\n  <object class=\"tableauViz\" style=\"display:none;\">\n    <param name=\"host_url\" value=\"https%3A%2F%2Fpublic.tableau.com%2F\">\n    <param name=\"embed_code_version\" value=\"3\">\n    <param name=\"site_root\" value=\"\">\n    <param name=\"name\" value=\"WaterusevsrechargeofgroundwaterinYucatan/BLEWF\">\n    <param name=\"tabs\" value=\"no\">\n    <param name=\"toolbar\" value=\"yes\">\n    <param name=\"static_image\" value=\"https://public.tableau.com/static/images/Wa/WaterusevsrechargeofgroundwaterinYucatan/BLEWF/1.png\">\n    <param name=\"animate_transition\" value=\"yes\">\n    <param name=\"display_static_image\" value=\"yes\">\n    <param name=\"display_spinner\" value=\"yes\">\n    <param name=\"display_overlay\" value=\"yes\">\n    <param name=\"display_count\" value=\"yes\">\n    <param name=\"language\" value=\"en-GB\">\n  </object>\n</div>\n<script type=\"text/javascript\">\n  var divElement = document.getElementById('viz2003');\n  var vizElement = divElement.getElementsByTagName('object')[0];\n  if (divElement.offsetWidth > 800) { vizElement.style.width = '100%'; vizElement.style.height = '827px'; }\n  else if (divElement.offsetWidth > 500) { vizElement.style.width = '100%'; vizElement.style.height = '827px'; }\n  else { vizElement.style.width = '100%'; vizElement.style.height = '727px